The White House Chief of Staff, Denis McDonough, and Deputy National Security Advisor for Strategic Communications, Ben Rhodes, recently met with leaders from the Armenian Assembly of America and the Armenian National Committee of America. The purpose of the meeting was to discuss the upcoming centennial commemoration of the 1915 atrocities against Armenians. McDonough and Rhodes emphasized the importance of honoring the 1.5 million lives lost during that period and praised the advocacy efforts of the Armenian American community. They pledged that the United States will use this occasion to push for a full and just acknowledgement of the facts surrounding the atrocities. Additionally, President Obama has asked Treasury Secretary Jacob J. Lew to lead a Presidential Delegation to Yerevan on April 24th to stand in solidarity with the Armenian people during this solemn anniversary.